ce:section.ce:para:
As the discrimination of complex samples such as mixtures is a big challenge for array sensing, the ability of our sensor array for discriminating mixtures of three metal ions (Hg2+, Cu2+, Fe3+) were further tested. Three carbon dots successfully discriminated all the combinations (Fig. 6
                        ). Because the total concentration of the metal ions was fixed to 100μM, one can naturally expect that the response of the sensing array in the presence of two metal ions should be between the responses of each metal ions. Although this is true for most of the cases, we observed that in some cases it is more complicated (Fig. 7
                        ). For example, the response of the binary of Fe3+ and Hg2+ is higher than that of Fe3+ and Hg2+ ions only. In the blind study, 40 blind samples can be successfully identified and the discrimination accuracy was found to be 100% (see the Supporting information, Tables S8 and S9).
